## Review Guidelines

### Correctness & Safety
- Logic errors, off-by-one, unchecked null/nil/None dereference
- Exception/error swallowing
- Hardcoded credentials, API keys, private keys in source

### Security
- Injection (SQL, command, template)
- Missing authz checks on sensitive operations
- Insecure defaults in configuration

### Performance & Operations
- Obvious N+1 or unbounded loops on I/O
- Missing timeouts on network calls
- Resource leaks (connections, file handles)

### Maintainability
- Confusing public API changes without documentation
- Dead code paths that hide bugs

## Scoring

- **90-100**: Clean code, no significant issues
- **70-89**: Minor issues only
- **50-69**: Moderate issues
- **30-49**: Serious issues
- **0-29**: Critical issues requiring immediate fix

